  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But always Berlin hyphen or whatever the district was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Walked.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We walked.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We walked.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not a long walk between the other house and this house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe I, I-- when we were changing tapes, I was talking about the-- in answer to your question about other causes of fear, if I may just complete that--",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--that story.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the stormtroopers would, would roam the streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I say roam, it wasn't anything random.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was very military-type marching.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they carried this Blood Flag.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the-- every passerby, everybody on the street, had to stand at attention and give the Hitler salute.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [LAUGHS] I wasn't going to be caught dead giving this Hitler salute.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If you didn't give the Hitler salute, there were a couple of bullies-- or more than a couple-- marching at the side of the corps looking out that everybody really did salute.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And anybody that didn't got beaten up, and depending on their mood, either badly or lightly or just given a kick in the behind, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Whatever their mood was, they were the boss.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, I didn't want to give the salute.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I also didn't want to get beaten up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I became a master at discovering doorways, hidey-holes of that kind when I saw them coming.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they were pretty noisy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were either singing their party songs and-- or they were-- well, one of the most popular party songs was, 'When Jewish blood splashes from the knife'-- I'm giving you word-by-word translation. 'When Jewish blood splashes from the knife, things go twice as well'-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] just a little illustration.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
